          </m:mfenced>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:munderover>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mi>i</m:mi>
              <m:mo>=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>1</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:munderover>
          <m:mi mathvariant="double-struck">E</m:mi>
          <m:mfenced separators="" open="(" close=")">
            <m:msubsup>
              <m:mi>X</m:mi>
              <m:mi>i</m:mi>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msubsup>
          </m:mfenced>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:munderover>
            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mi>i</m:mi>
              <m:mo>=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>1</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:munderover>
          <m:msup>
            <m:mi>σ</m:mi>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
          </m:msup>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          <m:msup>
            <m:mi>σ</m:mi>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
          </m:msup>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
    <para id="id263551">and hence <link target-id="uid5"/> holds. We now turn to <link target-id="uid6"/> and <link target-id="uid7"/>. Let us first consider <link target-id="uid7"/>. We begin by applying Markov's inequality:</para>
    <equation id="uid8"><m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
